"For the radial profile of satellite galaxies, we as-
sume that satellite galaxies follow a Navarro-Frenk-White
(NFW) profile [50] that is an approximated model of the
averaged dark matter profile in halos. To compute the
NFW profile as a function of halo mass, redshift and cos-
