AND SDSS-LIKE GALAXIES
"In this paper we use two types of mock catalogs
of SDSS- and HSC-like galaxies. First, we use high-
resolution N -body simulations, with periodic boundary
conditions, and the halo catalogs to generate the mock
catalogs of SDSS galaxies. We then measure ∆Σ and wp
from the mock catalogs to define the mock signals that
we use in cosmology challenges. Second, we also use the
mock catalogs of SDSS- and HSC-like galaxies built in
the light-cone simulations, including the simulated lens-
