It is clear that wp has a grater S/N value than ∆Σ does
by a factor of 4, because of the much wider area coverage
of SDSS data compared to the HSC-Y1 data by a factor
of 60. Nevertheless, we will show later that combining
∆Σ and wp is crucial to lift parameter degeneracies and
obtain useful cosmological constraints."
