"IV. METHODOLOGY FOR COSMOLOGY
CHALLENGES"
"The purpose of this paper is to study whether the halo
model based method can recover the true cosmological
parameters from a hypothetical parameter inference, i.e.
comparing the theoretical templates with the mock sig-
nals, taking into account the error covariance in the like-
lihood analysis. Here we describe our methodology to
perform cosmology challenges. We employ different se-
tups of the analysis method to quantify the impact of
various effects on cosmological parameter estimation, and
describe each setup and its purpose."
